The paper discusses the development of concurrent software using choreographic programming, which falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also focuses on preventing deadlocks, which is a common issue in distributed computing (cs.DC) and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper formalizes the properties that an asynchronous semantics for choreographies should have, which involves the study of distributed systems (cs.DS) and logic (cs.LO).
